You solve Advent of Code problems every day during December. After solving a 
problem, you want your system to automatically organize everything instead of
doing it manually. 

The system will be able to fetch the puzzle, help you in
understanding the puzzle. 

After user solved the puzzle he can paste code, select day, part and it will 
organize the folder structure by day and year, create code file(part1 & part2 
separately) and produce a README that includes both the problem explanation 
(either AI-generated or manually added) and your personal approach to solve puzzle
optionally will be written by only user will be added to README.md of each day.
It will also maintain a parent README.md file which will overall information about the 
Advent of code, links to problems solved code in github, link to question etc.

Taking the above information It will automatically publish results to 
GitHub: creating commits, pushing daily changes, tagging versions.

User can also generate social-sharing content/Post using the information
so that after completing a puzzle, user can instantly post about it on 
Twitter/LinkedIn/etc.

